cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial expression recognition using 4D face scan data. The use of deep learning techniques such as convolutional layers and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of rank pooling to generate dynamic images could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The focus on facial expressions and their recognition could also suggest a connection to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning for classification could also place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
